  { q: `What is the HSK exam?`, a: `The HSK (Hanyu Shuiping Kaoshi) is the standardized Chinese proficiency test recognized by governments and universities worldwide. It has 6 main levels: HSK 1 (150 words, beginner) through HSK 6 (5,000+ words, advanced). The exam tests listening, reading, and writing. A separate HSKK oral exam tests speaking ability.` },
  { q: `How long does it take to pass HSK 3?`, a: `With consistent daily study of 1-2 hours, most learners reach HSK 3 within 6-12 months. This requires learning about 600 vocabulary words, basic grammar structures, and developing reading and listening skills. Students in intensive programs (4+ hours/day) often reach HSK 3 in 3-4 months.` },
  { q: `Is HSK accepted for university admission in China?`, a: `Yes. Most Chinese universities require HSK 4 (score 180+) or HSK 5 for international student admission. Chinese government scholarships (CSC) typically require HSK 4-5. Some technical or science programs accept HSK 3 since courses may be taught in English. The exact requirement depends on the university and program.` },
  { q: `How much does the HSK exam cost?`, a: `Prices vary by country and level. In mainland China, HSK 1-2 costs about 200-300 RMB, HSK 3-4 about 400-500 RMB, and HSK 5-6 about 550-800 RMB. In the US and Europe, prices range from $30-65 USD per level. Tests are offered multiple times per year at authorized test centers worldwide.` },
